{
  "texts": [
    "The authors demonstrate that the method is effective both in mitigating bias for the gender-profession domain as well as in generalizing these influences to other unseen domains.",
    "However, the work only addresses gender bias in masked LLMs and it remains uncertain whether the proposed method can be generalized to other kinds of LLMs and more complex social biases like race and social class discrimination.",
    "These methods build on the idea that an LLM can be decomposed into task-specific vectors.",
    "Then the vector of the task to be forgotten can be eliminated to achieve unlearning.",
    "Ilharco et al (2022) introduce a novel paradigm for steering neural network behavior based on task vectors."
  ]
}